summary: You've probably answered this before but, what's your opinion on how Andi "acts". Like some people argue she is a "brat", while...
question: You've probably answered this before but, what's your opinion on how Andi "acts". Like some people argue she is a "brat", while others argue she is "correct to feel those ways". What's your stance on this matter?
answer: I think she’s a 13 year old acting like a 13 year old. She’s had a tough time and a lot of her reactions are valid and to be expected to be honest. There are elements of selfishness to her character but that’s something she seems to be growing out of, which is the whole point of a character arc. I’ve seen a lot of people complain about how dramatic she is but honestly? Accurate representation of a young teenager imo.

summary: Buffy And Andi: Roommate Headcanons
body:
Buffy And Andi: Roommate Headcanons

- Always making random noises from across the apartment at each other

- Andi always waking up first and making Buffy coffee for whenever she inevitably stumbles out of bed twice as grouchy as usual

- Both of them losing their minds when they see a spider and abandoning whichever room it’s in for the next two+ hours

- Bursting into one another’s bedrooms to yell about whatever gossip they’ve just heard at weird times in the night

- Covering each other with blankets when one of them falls asleep on the couch

- Leaving each other little note reminders about washing the dishes or buying more milk

- Getting mad and smacking the ceiling with a broom when the apartment above is inevitably too loud

- Andi keeps getting locked out even though she swears she remembered to take her key

- Early morning dancing in the kitchen with the radio turned up as they make breakfast together

summary: Achromatic: Tyrus- Part 4
body:
Achromatic: Tyrus- Part 4

—Time jump to when Andi and Amber saw TJ and Cyrus through window and thought they were being cute—

Cyrus ran around the school.

Cyrus: “Where could he be? When either one of us is feeling upset we both go to- THAT’S IT!! THE SWINGS!! He would never skip school to go to the park though, would he?”

That’s when Cyrus remembered the strike. Last year students were skipping school or going late far too often in order to catch up on sleep rather than school work. They organized a strike- they stood behind the school where there was nothing but grass and picnic tables. They stood there and protested that they get a one hour block of free time. On that very same land, a park was built. If students stopped skipping or coming late, demands would be met- and so they were. Once the park was built, the students got to name it. Cyrus remembered this. He ran to the nearest exit and ran to the school park. He stopped in his tracks when he saw the sign. A warm feeling grew inside him. “GHC Park” the students named the park after the leaders of the protest- they haven’t forgotten about the dress code protest. Cyrus looked around and saw a sullen TJ sitting on the swings: arms holding the chains, feet softly kicking the ground, and eyes staring at nothing in the distance. Cyrus walked up to him with a hollow heart and a twisted stomach.

Cyrus: “Hey, TJ.”

TJ: “No.”

Cyrus: “Excuse me?”

TJ: “No. Leave me alone alright? Haven’t you done enough damage?”

Cyrus: “TJ I’m here because I haven’t forgotten.”

TJ: “Haven’t forgotten what?”

Cyrus: “You don’t understand I like you like you?”

TJ: “Oh, well consider those feelings gone. I’m just empty.”

Cyrus: “I would say how come but I already know the answer. I’m so sorry. I’m sorry about being so rude, I’m sorry for hurting your feelings, I’m sorry TJ. I’m so sorry.”

Cyrus began to tear up and choke on his words.

Cyrus: “I’m sorry. I don’t deserve you.”

TJ: “Hell yeah you don’t.”

And with that, Cyrus began to walk away in defeat.

TJ thought to himself: “Nice one TJ! Anything good you gotta ruin it! You still like him dumbass! Don’t let him leave!!”

TJ: “Cyrus!!!! Wait!!!!”

Cyrus walked back.

Cyrus: “You aren’t done yelling at me?”

TJ: “I’m not going to yell, just…. Question.”

Cyrus: “Okay.. Go ahead.”

TJ: “Who was that guy? The day I helped you try to open my locker? He run up to you and hugged you?”

Cyrus let out a wild laugh.

TJ: “I don’t get it.”

Cyrus: “Calm down T-Jealous! That’s my cosuin Benjamin. He’s just really tall for an 11 year old. He is visiting from Canada and I haven’t seen him since he was 6 so it came as a surprise to see him.”

TJ felt like the worlds biggest idiot. Again.

TJ: “I’m sorry I just jumped to conclusions. That still doesn’t explain the key I found.”

He took the key out of his pocket.

TJ: “You dropped it. What is it for?”

Cyrus began to stutter anxiously.

Cyrus: “It’s uHH for uh my you know how everyone has a key for that thing that they do with that thing on the thing with the thing for your uhh d- d- dog.”

TJ: “Cyrus, you don’t have a dog. Also literally none of that was English.”

Cyrus: “Look I can’t tell you what it’s for.. It’s.. A surprise.”

TJ: Another surprise? The last one gave me food poisoning!”

Cyrus: “Yeah I’m sorry about that but you’ll like this one.”

TJ: “Oh! You’ll be needing the key.”

Cyrus: “No, you can open it when you see it.”

TJ: “What IS IT?”

Cyrus: “No.”

TJ: “Cyrus, come on!”

Cyrus: “I said no.”

TJ: “You can be a little annoying you know that?”

Cyrus: “Well, you can be oblivious.”

TJ: “Well you can be very judgey.”

Cyrus: “Well, you can be intimidating.”

TJ: You know what else you are?”

Cyrus: “What?”

TJ: “The only-“

Cyrus knew, he joined in.

TJ and Cyrus: “Person I can talk to like this.”

The boys smiled at how close they were.

“Just do it. Stop lying, now is your time come on.” Both thought. So they did.

TJ and Cyrus: “I was lying. Wait what? You go first! No I’ll go first! Fine you go!”

They had to break up this madness. They yelled random words until the synchronization was broken.

TJ and Cyrus: “Swings! Muffins! Somersault! Barracuda! Sorry I was thinking about Finding Nemo. YOOOO!!!! Okay I know right! Like bro! IT. ATE. HER!! Okay but seriously we need to break this. Challah! You have pretty eyes! Wait what? Really? Yeah. AWW! Oh my GOD someone please end this.”

They kept going for another minute until they both said the same thing that left the other boy speechless.

TJ and Cyrus: “I think.. I’m in love with you.”

They blinked hard and backed up.

Cyrus: “I- don’t know what to say.”

TJ: “I don’t eith- AHH GOD I HATE YOU!”

Cyrus: “What? You- you hate me?”

TJ: “AGH not you! That bee! A bee just stung me!”

Cyrus: “Hold still, let me get the stinger out.”

Cyrus held TJ’s wrist and gently pulled out the stinger.

TJ winced and let tears escape his misty eyes.

TJ: “That bee is stupid.”

Cyrus: “Well without their pollen we would not-“

TJ: “Cyrus!”

Cyrus: “But that bee is stupid. Let me take you to the nurse.”

TJ: “Thanks I appreciate it.”

Cyrus: “Anytime. Just another service I provide.”




Stan List✨: @tj-is-tgay @swingsetsandmuffins @tyrusflavoredtea @gal4xyfalls @luzawithoutu @annielovestyrus @outhereshippingtyrus @ammaranth324 @all-about-the-mack @lovefortyrus @yo-quiero-more-iero @judgemental-llama @softambi
